go-to: ministries

We have decided to drop this concession.

@drop_foreclosure
title: Impose a rent moratorium and postpone the foreclosure of insolvent farms
subtitle: Drop this concession +2 budget
tags: drop_demands
choose-if: tax_breaks = 1 
view-if: tax_breaks = 1
on-arrival: rpm_points -= 5; tax_breaks -= 1; budget += 2; ddp_relation += 5; dvp_relation += 5; ddp_right -= 1; economic_growth -= 0.5
go-to: ministries

We have decided to drop this concession.


@low
on-arrival: pro_republic += 3; nationalism -= 3*(1-dissent); dnvp_relation += 5; z_catholic += 4*(1-dissent); dnvp_rural += 5; z_rural += 2*(1-dissent); right_dissent -= 5; cnblp_formed += 1
face-image: img/portraits/HergtOscar.jpg

After substantial concessions to the Landvolkbewegung, most farmers are content for now, as is the <span style="color: #000000;">**VdB**</span>, but the more radical elements still agitate against our policies. However, our worker base is unhappy with our capitulation to organised agriculture. In light of rising worker unemployment, this focus on agricultural issues is viewed as blatant pandering to the <span style="color: #385A38;">**RLB**</span> and <span style="color: #000000;">**VdB**</span>. 

Despite the successful talks, Karl Hepp from the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and elements from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP's**</span> <span style="color: #385A38;">agrarian</span> wing have formed a new political party called the <span style="color: #909090;">**CNBLP**</span> in response to the preeminence of industrial interests in the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>. Although the Rural People’s Movement has been pacified, the <span style="color: #909090;">**CNBLP's**</span> appeal as an <span style="color: #385A38;">agrarian</span> <span style="color: #909090;">**special interest**</span> party can only spell trouble for the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> in the upcoming elections.

@medium
on-arrival: pro_republic -= 2; nationalism += 2*(1-dissent); dnvp_relation -= 4; nsdap_rural += 4; dnvp_rural -= 3; z_rural -= 1; z_catholic += 3; right_dissent += 5; rpm_strength += 1; cnblp_formed += 1
face-image: img/portraits/WestarpKuno.jpg

Despite some concessions to the Landvolkbewegung, some feel that our policies do not go far enough in helping German farmers, but the <span style="color: #000000;">**VdB**</span>  is satisfied with our handling of the situation. As such, the radical elements of the movement have been significantly empowered and will seek to use this initially moderate movement to resort to increasingly violent acts of protest. This will have a destabilising effect in the countryside and may serve to further radicalise the already disenfranchised rural electorate.

Meanwhile, Karl Hepp from the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> has formed a new political party called the <span style="color: #909090;">**CNBLP**</span> along with elements from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP's**</span> <span style="color: #385A38;">agrarian</span> wing in response to the preeminence of industrial interests in the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>. With its appeal as an <span style="color: #385A38;">agrarian</span> <span style="color: #909090;">**special interest**</span> party, this can only spell trouble for the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> in the upcoming elections

@high
on-arrival: pro_republic -= 5; nationalism += 5*(1-dissent); dnvp_relation -= 8; nsdap_rural += 7; z_rural -= 3; dnvp_rural -= 4; nsdap_catholic += 5; z_catholic -= 4; dnvp_catholic -= 1; right_dissent -= 8; rpm_strength += 2; cnblp_formed += 1
face-image: img/portraits/WestarpKuno.jpg

Talks with the Landvolkbewegung have broken down due to our refusal to offer them any substantial concessions, much to the disapproval of the <span style="color: #000000;">**VdB**</span>. As such, the radical elements of the movement have been significantly empowered and will seek to use this initially moderate movement to resort to increasingly violent acts of protest. This will have a destabilising effect in the countryside and may serve to further radicalise the already disenfranchised rural electorate.

Meanwhile, Karl Hepp from the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and elements from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP's**</span> <span style="color: #385A38;">agrarian</span> wing have formed a political party called the <span style="color: #909090;">**CNBLP**</span> in response to the preeminence of industrial interests in the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>. With the growing strength of the Rural People’s Movement and the <span style="color: #909090;">**CNBLP's**</span> appeal as an <span style="color: #385A38;">agrarian</span> <span style="color: #909090;">**special interest**</span> party, this can only spell trouble for the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> in the upcoming elections


